title: black energy as the basis of the known universe
description:
The document is published in dutch. Some thinking of me from years ago of how black energy could be the basis of everything in the univere as we know it. Everything is bases on zero-point particles and everything we see in he physical world is based on swirling connections of intereacting zero-point based particles.

Included are two borland c programs written for dos. One is a dynamic newtonian-based model, the other is a einsteinian photo snaphot of black energy.
Both can be run using dosbox.

For everyone to read and to find out if it is interesting and if it may include a part of the truth about everything in the universe as we know it is based on zero-point particles which are infinte in bending of space but have no length, width or height.

If anyone is interested please give me some comments about this. I do have more programs. One interesting program is written in qbasic showing the distance of electrons swirling an neutron-proton core of an atom.
